{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":238358,"duration_api_ms":233852,"num_turns":2,"result":"## core_business_v2/ingestion Module Overview\n\n### REST Endpoints (4 controllers)\n\n| Controller | Method | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **IngestionController** | `POST` | `/api/v1/ingestion/events` | Main ingestion entry point |\n| | `GET` | `/api/v1/ingestion/health-check` | Health check |\n| **EntityController** | `POST` | `/api/v1/entities/query` | Query failed entities (paginated) |\n| | `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}` | Get entity by ID |\n| | `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` | Get display status |\n| **FingerprintController** | `POST` | `/api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` | Calculate entity fingerprint |\n| **PolicyController** | `POST` | `/api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` | Mark all entities for policy reprocessing |\n\n### Request Processing Flow\n\n```\nPOST /api/v1/ingestion/events\n    │\n    ▼\nIngestionController\n    ├── Generate requestId (16-char hex)\n    ├── Register callback (CompletableFuture with 60s timeout)\n    ├── Publish to Redis INGESTION_INTERNAL_STREAM\n    └── Return Mono<ResultDTO> (reactive, non-blocking)\n    │\n    ▼\nIngestionInternalConsumer (Redis Stream consumer group, 16 consumers × 32 workers)\n    ├── Parse IngestionRequest from stream\n    └── Call IngestionOrchestrator.process()\n    │\n    ▼\nIngestionOrchestrator (routing logic)\n    ├── Check EntityCache (Redis) for existing entity\n    │   ├── CACHE HIT → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n    │   └── CACHE MISS → Acquire CREATE_LOCK\n    │       ├── Query DB\n    │       │   ├── Found → DbExistingEntityHandler\n    │       │   └── Not found → NewEntityHandler\n    │       └── Lock failure → Requeue with exponential backoff\n    │\n    ▼\nHandler Selection (fingerprint-based for existing entities):\n    ├── NewEntityHandler: create entity, cache, acquire PROCESS_LOCK, run state machine\n    ├── SameAttr + Lock: return entity as-is (no reprocessing needed)\n    ├── SameAttr + NoLock: poll every 500ms until other request completes\n    ├── DiffAttr + Lock: reset to PENDING, re-run state machine\n    └── DiffAttr + NoLock: interrupt running SM, acquire lock, reset, re-run\n    │\n    ▼\nEntityStateMachine.start()\n    ├── PENDING  → LabelService.label()      → LABELED\n    ├── LABELED  → PolicyService.evaluate()   → EVALUATED\n    ├── EVALUATED → EnforcementService.enforce() → ENFORCED\n    └── Each stage: max 3 retries, backoff 1-3s + jitter, separate @Transactional\n    │\n    ▼\nIngestionCallbackRegistry.complete(requestId, result)\n    └── CompletableFuture resolves → REST response returned to caller\n```\n\n### State Machine (EntityStateMachine)\n\n**States**: `PENDING` → `LABELED` → `EVALUATED` → `ENFORCED`\n\nEach transition:\n- Wrapped in its own `@Transactional` via `EntityStageTransactionRunner`\n- Max 3 retries with increasing backoff (1s, 2s, 3s + jitter)\n- Distinguishes retryable vs non-retryable error codes\n- Checks `interrupted` flag between stages (allows preemption by newer requests)\n- Persists stage progress to DB after each successful transition\n- Merges stage results into a cumulative JSON `processingResult`\n- Has failpoints (`SM_BEFORE_SERVICE_*`, `SM_AFTER_SERVICE_*`) for crash testing\n\n### Key Architectural Patterns\n\n1. **Redis Streams** for reliable message delivery (external → internal pipeline)\n2. **Distributed locks** (CREATE_LOCK + PROCESS_LOCK) for concurrency control\n3. **Fingerprint-based routing** — SHA256 of ~40 host fields + ~35 user fields determines if entity attributes changed\n4. **Callback registry** bridges async stream processing back to synchronous REST responses\n5. **Version ordering** via Redis stream IDs to skip stale requests\n6. **Interrupt mechanism** — newer requests with different attributes can preempt running state machines\n7. **Recovery service** — scheduled scan finds stuck entities (non-ENFORCED, code=0, stale timestamp) and retriggers them\n8. **Policy reprocess job** — scheduled + event-driven scan marks entities as INIT for bulk re-evaluation\n\n### Entity Model\n\nThe core `Entity` table tracks: type (HOST or USER_HOST_BINDING), identity keys (hostId, userId, adapterId), processing state (stage + code + errorMessage + JSON result), attribute fingerprint (SHA256), version (stream ID), interrupted flag, and reprocess state.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"0aafb144-84ef-4f87-a69e-b61e74322c76","total_cost_usd":0.6332057,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22855,"cache_read_input_tokens":36939,"output_tokens":1597,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":22855,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1597,"cacheReadInputTokens":36939,"cacheCreationInputTokens":22855,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20125825,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":120,"outputTokens":21197,"cacheReadInputTokens":1766762,"cacheCreationInputTokens":119333,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.43194745,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ac76197b-ff42-4b1d-9b0f-be4dc485fcb9"}
